gomodel:SYNGO_5495  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 5: confocal and super-resolution immunofluorescence imaging of ATR in 21DIV cultured cortical neurons showed co-localization with Clathrin and β-adaptin at synaptic puncta.\n\nFigure 6, S5: super-resolution microscopy showed ATR co-localized with PSD95 (DLG4) and chromogranin-A (a DCV marker), but also in close proximity to Bassoon (BSN) in 21DIV cultured cortical neurons.\n\nFigure 7, S6: super-resolution microscopy showed ATR co-localized with VGAT but not VGLUT in 21DIV cultured cortical neurons. ATR pulldowns yield VGAT but not VGLUT.\n\nauthors summarise;\n\"Taken together, these data strongly suggest that ATM is located in association with excitatory vesicles, while ATR is associated with inhibitory vesicles, consistent with their differential effects on the E/I balance in our cultures.\". Experimental description: M&M: \"Cultures of mouse cortical neurons were prepared from\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-20" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5495" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

